  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db8 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Badiuddin's petition is adjourned to January",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Supreme Court has fixed today (05) to consider the appeal filed by Mr. Rishad Badiuddin from the Court of Appeal to revoke the order given by the Court of Appeal to re-cultivate the illegally cleared forests of Wilpattu at his own expense.",
        "This appeal was considered before a Supreme Court bench consisting of Mr. Gamini Amarasekara, Achala Vengappuli and Mr. Arjuna Obeysekera.",
        "Mr. Arjuna Obeysekera, who is a member of this three-member Supreme Court bench, has also participated in the appeal court hearing of this case, so it is proper to refer this appeal petition to another Supreme Court bench for consideration.",
        "The Environmental Justice Center had filed a writ petition against the former minister Mr. Rishad Badiuddin in the Court of Appeal, alleging that he illegally cleared the forests and built villages in the vicinity of Wilpattu forest. Dissatisfied with that order, the former minister filed an appeal petition before the Supreme Court requesting that the relevant order be annulled."
      ],
